This app uses FastAPI for the backend and Streamlit for the front end.  See api and app directories respectively.

Setup:
create a .env file using the example. FAST_API_URL is only nessisary when deploying to production, defaults to localhost:8000. external APIs can be tested with tests/hello_openai.py.  To be able to delete default documents create a secure ADMIN_TOKEN

Requirements are in requirements.txt and can be built with pip install -r requirements.txt
pip install:
    streamlit
    python-dotenv
    fastapi 
    uvicorn
    langchain 
    langchain-openai 
    langchain-core 
    langchain-community 
    docx2txt 
    pypdf  
    langchain_chroma 
    sentence-transformers

Development Run:
    Build: pip install -r requirements.txt
    Start FastAPI Backend: uvicorn api.main:app --reload
    Start Streamlit Frontend: streamlit run app/streamlit_app.py

    Check FastAPI: http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs for api endpoints
    Streamlit UI:  http://localhost:8501/ for development frontend

Production Run:
Backend-
    Build Command: pip install -r requirements.txt
    Start Command: uvicorn api.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port $PORT

Frontend-
    Build Command: pip install -r requirements.txt
    Start Command: streamlit run app/streamlit_app.py --server.port $PORT --server.address 0.0.0.0
    
    
(two seperate services on render - backend api and frontend)


--ADMIN TOOLS--
added the ability to delete the default document by running a local script
Run the admin tool:
python admin_tools.py